Since it looks like we actually fetch the nodes (https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/commit/1d93668c0e5e8bf91aa70f92c998bd34d548c2e7), we can probably ensure that children of other nodes being commented are not included. This will prevent the following case:

<img width="258" alt="screen shot 2017-06-01 at 11 14 57 am" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2193314/26694217/90e8655e-46bb-11e7-9fa2-714a3507e65a.png">

<img width="253" alt="screen shot 2017-06-01 at 11 16 00 am" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2193314/26694263/b6bee212-46bb-11e7-9538-6dfaf865271c.png">

I expect the following result:

```css
/*.foo {
    display: block;
}*/
/*.bar {
    .foo {
        display: block;
    }
}*/
```

I use a debug configuration to run my mocha tests. This is my current configuration in my `.vscode/launch.json`:

    {
        // Use IntelliSense to learn about possible Node.js debug attributes.
        // Hover to view descriptions of existing attributes.
        // For more information, visit: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=830387
        "version": "0.2.0",
        "configurations": [
            {
                "type": "node",
                "request": "launch",
                "name": "Mocha Tests",
                "program": "${workspaceRoot}/node_modules/mocha/bin/_mocha",
                "args": [
                    "-u",
                    "tdd",
                    "--timeout",
                    "999999",
                    "--colors",
                    "${workspaceRoot}/test/**/*.spec.js"
                ],
                "internalConsoleOptions": "openOnSessionStart"
            }
        ]
    }

When I run the `Mocha Tests`, the debug panel always remains open even if all the tests succeed. I'd like it to automatically close the panel when all tests succeed (on `0` exit code) maybe even after n seconds. I envision a new config:

    {
        // Use IntelliSense to learn about possible Node.js debug attributes.
        // Hover to view descriptions of existing attributes.
        // For more information, visit: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=830387
        "version": "0.2.0",
        "configurations": [
            {
                "type": "node",
                "request": "launch",
                "name": "Mocha Tests",
                "program": "${workspaceRoot}/node_modules/mocha/bin/_mocha",
                "args": [
                    "-u",
                    "tdd",
                    "--timeout",
                    "999999",
                    "--colors",
                    "${workspaceRoot}/test/**/*.spec.js"
                ],
                "internalConsoleOptions": "openOnSessionStart",
                "closeConsoleOnSuccess": 5
            }
        ]
    }

Where `closeConsoleOnSuccess` could be a Boolean or a Number for number of seconds (or go with milliseconds) if you don't interact with the panel and it will close when exit code is `0`.
